						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Kulasēkharadēva, Year 22: 1290 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged in the middle and incomplete. It seems to record an undertaking by the <hi rend="italic">dēvākaṉmis</hi>, of Taṇḍēśura piḷḷaiyār temple at Kāriyēri <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Ulaguyyavandapāṇḍyanallūr in Amudaguṇa-vaḷanāḍu, who is stated to have received some gift from a certain Seṅkaṉ (Sokkaṉ) <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Śeraṉai-veṉṟāṉ to burn a perpetual lamp in the temple.</p>						

